raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pygsi" %}
{% set version = "0.6.5" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/DIRACGrid/pyGSI/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: e04f00cd14a7320fd654e4886be6dfdeae91e8b76935e530edbe42898be92bac

build:
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv"
  skip: true  # [not (unix and py2k)]

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - openssl =1.0
  run:
    - python
    - openssl =1.0

test:
  imports:
    - GSI
    - GSI.crypto
    - GSI.rand
    - GSI.SSL

about:
  home: https://github.com/DIRACGrid/pyGSI
  license: GPL-3.0
  license_family: GPL
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Python interface for GSI authentication'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - chrisburr
